<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="67" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1548,2005]" pageId="8" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,286,1548,1573]" pageId="8" pageNumber="67">Etymology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gonçalves &amp; Souto &amp; Mermudes &amp; Silveira" authorityYear="2019" box="[296,419,1549,1572]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Uanauna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angaporan">
<emphasis box="[296,419,1549,1572]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="67">angaporan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a composite word, gender neutral, name in apposition. From Tupi-guarani language 
<emphasis box="[151,207,1585,1608]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="67">anga</emphasis>
, a corrupted form of 
<emphasis box="[446,502,1585,1608]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="67">angá</emphasis>
, surprise; 
<emphasis box="[620,687,1585,1608]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="67">poran</emphasis>
, a corrupted form of 
<emphasis box="[926,1021,1585,1608]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="67">poranga</emphasis>
, beautiful (
<bibRefCitation author="Barbosa, A. L." box="[1149,1309,1584,1609]" pageId="8" pageNumber="67" pagination="1 - 202" refId="ref6765" refString="Barbosa, A. L. (1951) Pequeno dicionario tupi-portugues. Com quatro apendices: Perfil da lingua tupi, Palavras compostas e derivadas, Metaplasmos, Sintese bibliografica. Livraria Sao Jose, Rio de Janeiro, 1951, 1 - 202." type="journal article" year="1951">Barbosa 1951</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="67" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1548,2005]" pageId="8" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1620,1645]" pageId="8" pageNumber="67">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
body size around 
<quantity box="[525,586,1620,1645]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="6.0">6mm</quantity>
; elytra (
<figureCitation box="[676,781,1620,1645]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–3" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1718,1740]" captionTargetBox="[363,1248,939,1676]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[332,1254,929,1696]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–3. Uanauna angaporan sp. nov. male habitus: 2, dorsal; 3, ventral. Scale bar: 1mm (2–3)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2636234/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="67">Figs. 2, 3</figureCitation>
, 42,43) brown to black with 3/4 of length and 2/5 of width of external lateral margins yellow-pale when elytra brown or white when elytra black, subparallel, lightly rounded. Male sternum IX (
<figureCitation box="[363,499,1692,1717]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–41" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1393,1415]" captionTargetBox="[206,1358,683,1331]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[184,1399,661,1371]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 32–41. Uanauna angaporan sp. nov.: 32-34 male sternum IX, 32, ventral; 33, lateral; 34, oblique; 35–37 aedeagus, 35, dorsal; 36, lateral; 37, ventral; pygidium, 38, dorsal; 39–40, lateral; 41, ventral. Scale bar: 0.5mm (32–41)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2636248/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="67">Figs. 32–34</figureCitation>
) with lateral margins asymmetric, left margin divergent anteriad until ¼ length of plaque in ventral view, right margin divergent until 3/4 length in ventral view, then convergent, posterior margin slightly sinuous in ventral view; syntergite symmetric, as long as 1/2 core sternum IX length, anterior margin strongly indented, posterior margin rounded.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="68" pageId="8" pageNumber="67" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1548,2005]" pageId="8" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1836,1861]" pageId="8" pageNumber="67">Description.</emphasis>
Body length ca. 
<quantity box="[535,593,1836,1861]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="6.0">6mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[608,714,1836,1861]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–3" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1718,1740]" captionTargetBox="[363,1248,939,1676]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[332,1254,929,1696]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–3. Uanauna angaporan sp. nov. male habitus: 2, dorsal; 3, ventral. Scale bar: 1mm (2–3)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2636234/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="67">Figs. 2, 3</figureCitation>
). Colour pattern brown to black except for 3/4 of length and 2/5 of width of external lateral margins yellow-pale when elytra brown to white when elytra black, and sternum VIII with a pair of spots of the rudimentary larval lanterns on sternum VIII (
<figureCitation box="[950,1057,1908,1933]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–3" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1718,1740]" captionTargetBox="[363,1248,939,1676]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[332,1254,929,1696]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–3. Uanauna angaporan sp. nov. male habitus: 2, dorsal; 3, ventral. Scale bar: 1mm (2–3)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2636234/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="67">Figs. 2, 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1069,1101,1909,1933]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–31" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1633,1655]" captionTargetBox="[422,1147,1218,1593]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[392,1178,1201,1611]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 29–31. Uanauna angaporan sp. nov.: 29–31, abdomen, 29, lateral; 30, ventral; 31, oblique. Scale bar:1mm (29– 31)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2636246/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="67">30</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1548,2005]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="68" pageId="8" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,1944,1969]" pageId="8" pageNumber="67">Male.</emphasis>
Posterior margin of pygidium emarginate in dorsal view; syntergite symmetric, as long as 1/2 core sternum IX length, anterior margin strongly indented, posterior margin rounded; sternum IX (
<figureCitation box="[1286,1428,1980,2005]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–41" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1393,1415]" captionTargetBox="[206,1358,683,1331]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[184,1399,661,1371]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 32–41. Uanauna angaporan sp. nov.: 32-34 male sternum IX, 32, ventral; 33, lateral; 34, oblique; 35–37 aedeagus, 35, dorsal; 36, lateral; 37, ventral; pygidium, 38, dorsal; 39–40, lateral; 41, ventral. Scale bar: 0.5mm (32–41)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2636248/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="67">Figs. 32–34</figureCitation>
) asymmetric, left margin divergent up to posterior 1/4, right margin divergent until 3/4 length in ventral view, anterior margin rounded, slightly sinuose in ventral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
